Study of the duration of antimicrobial chemotherapy in mycoplasmal pneumonia. We assessed the period of administration of antibiotics required for cases of mycoplasmal pneumonia. The subjects were 38 patients with mycoplasmal pneumonia admitted to our hospital. These patients were treated with 100 mg minocycline or 500 mg erythromycin by intravenous infusion twice a day. They were divided into a 6 day-administration group (Group A 16 cases) and a 9 day-administration group (Group B